#: ../../source/scene.rst:2
msgid "Scene Setting"
msgstr "シーン設定"

#: ../../source/scene.rst:10
msgid ""
"**FPS**: Should be consistent with blender, the higher the fps, the "
"higher speed the scene will be. If you want your scene looks faster, you "
"can decrease to speed up the passage of time."
msgstr ""
"Blender と一致するべきです。fps が高いほど、シーンの速度も速くなる傾向があります。 "
"シーンをより速く見せたい場合は、値を減らして時間の経過を速くすることができます。"

#: ../../source/scene.rst:12
msgid "**Gravity**: The force parallel to the global Z axis is normally -9.81."
msgstr "**重力**: グローバル Z 軸に平行な力は通常 -9.81 です。"

#: ../../source/scene.rst:15
msgid ""
"**Sub Step Number**: Split one animation frame into multiple small "
"frames, and simulation them. Used to solve the penetration problem of "
"high-speed moving objects. This is performance heavy operation,if not "
"necessary, set it as 1."
msgstr ""
"**サブステップ数**: 1 つのアニメーション "
"フレームを複数の小さなフレームに分割し、シミュレーションします。高速移動するオブジェクトの貫通問題を解決するために使用されます。これはパフォーマンスに大きな負荷がかかる操作なので、必要ない場合は"
" 1 に設定してください。"

#: ../../source/scene.rst:17
msgid ""
"Sub step means more accurate simulation, but sometimes you may find that "
"the rigidbody never end after increasing this, if this is not you want, "
"you can decrease sub step or increase damping."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scene.rst:19
msgid ""
"Never end movement issues explan: the inaccurate simulation means "
"inaccurate numerical calculation, which will lead the small number is "
"truncated, this means more energy is loosing over time. On the other "
"hand, too accurate means the energy that should be lost is retained, so "
"the simulation results show that it is more inclined to motion. If you "
"want something like the spring toy below, this is absolute you need."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scene.rst:27
msgid ""
"The video below shows when a high-speed object moving, increase the sub "
"step means the movement is split into small movement, so the rigidbody "
"can interact."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scene.rst:37
msgid ""
"**Position Iteration Number**: The higher the value, the more accurate "
"the location of the simulation results."
msgstr "**位置反復数**: 値が大きいほど、シミュレーション結果の位置がより正確になります。"

#: ../../source/scene.rst:39
msgid ""
"**Velocity Iteration Number**: The higher the value, the more accurate "
"the velocity of the simulation results."
msgstr "**速度反復数**: 値が大きいほど、シミュレーション結果の速度がより正確になります。"

#: ../../source/scene.rst:41
msgid ""
"A long rigidbody chain or model intersection need to increase iterations,"
" because long chains require iterative diffusion to obtain accurate "
"positions."
msgstr "長い剛体チェーンまたはモデルの交差では、正確な位置を取得するために反復拡散が必要になるため、反復を増やす必要があります。"

